<br>
<br>
To Lord Assassin Temeilion<br>
Halls House Fire and Fury<br>
Into his Hands with Utmost Discretion<br>
<br>
<br>
Vendui Lord Temeilion,<br>
<br>
I hereby approach you about the matter that I briefly mentioned to you earlier in the eve. It is a most delicate one and to be treated with discretion, a fact you are well used to in your work, I am sure.<br>
<br>
I do appreciate that you are a busy Assassin and the Duties to your House are many and should of course always come first. However, should you find some time in the next fortnight I would like to discuss with you a matter of information gathering and mayhap even acquisition regarding a Gnome doll.<br>
<br>
I have requested again and again that she be delivered to me, using my best manners and reasoning. Despite all my efforts I continue to be repudiated, and I think mayhap I may need some assistance. I have a Knight gathering information as well, as to where she may be kept.<br>
<br>
I will ofcourse reimburse you as I am able and I hope we can mayhap come to an agreement if you do not mind disalliancing yourself from some dwarves. There is no great rush, mind you, reply at your leisure. I thought to inquire with you as my regular Lady Assassin already is set on another task for me, regarding my Lizard Experiment.<br>
<br>
I do hope you had a fruitful and safe eve in the odd VexThal place, &amp; that you may have found there much fame and many riches. I remember well the conversation in which you explained this to be the path of reward for a Blade for Hire such as yourself.<br>
<br>
Thank you for taking this matter into your consideration.<br>
<br>
I remain, in the Meantime,<br>
<br>
Most Respectfully,<br>
<br>
